§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A subset $S ⊂ 𝗦_{++}^n$ of the cone of positive
    semidefinite matrices is a ❬spectrahedron❭ (or ❬real
    spectrahedron❭) if there exists an affine subset $M ⊂
    𝗦_{++}^n$ so that
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ S = 𝗦_{++}^n ∩ M ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

